  "explanation": "The defendant, an accountant with no prior criminal record, abused a position of trust to embezzle $25,000. However, mitigating factors include the lack of prior criminal history and the fact that the defendant has made partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and an attempt to rectify the harm caused. Under standard sentencing guidelines for a first-time white-collar offender involving this loss amount, an active prison sentence at the lower end of the spectrum is appropriate. The outburst from the spectator has no legal relevance to the sentencing process. A sentence of 6 months of incarceration balance deterrence, punishment, and the positive steps already taken towards rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
